---
description: Metrics, logs, and sentry conventions
alwaysApply: true
---

- Metrics names use `snake_case` and explicit units (`_seconds`, `_total`).
- Every new backend endpoint must emit at least one structured log with stable keys.
- Error paths must increment error counters and send 5xx failures to Sentry.
- Keep labels low-cardinality (`type`, `status`, `method`, `path`, `status_code`).
